Steps to install SQLite on Ubuntu

#sudo apt-get install sqlite3 libsqlite3-dev

Steps to create a database - geo - and to load the database schema

#cd src/main/resources
#sqlite3 geo.db
#sqlite> .read database.sql

Steps to show the tables available on the database geo

sqlite3 geo.db
sqlite> .tables
sqlite> select * from PositionInfo;


Clean table PositionInfo

sqlite3 geo.db
sqlite> DELETE FROM PositionInfo;